text: Cherlak () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Cherlakovsky Selsoviet, Dyurtyulinsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 584 as of 2010. There are 7 streets. == Geography == It is located 31 km from Dyurtyuli. == References == Category:Rural localities in Dyurtyulinsky District
title: Cherlak, Republic of Bashkortostan
